article.headline: Wright St 87, Belmont 79
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 26 points and Wright State rallied to beat Belmont 87-79 Saturday night. The Raiders (2-5) trailed by 10 with 11:38 to play. Tyrone Scott and Jaron Taylor each had 16 for Wright State. Wood finished 10-for-10 from the free-throw line. Justin Hare and Boomer Herndon led Belmont (3-5) with 18 points apiece, and Josh Goodwin added 17. Wright State had built an eight-point lead midway through the first half, but by halftime Belmont led 38-34 and expanded that to 10 until the Raiders rallied. There were six ties and six lead changes in the game.
